               <head>Final concord; Hinderclay, etc.; 1251</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> HINDERCLAY, &amp;c. Final concord at <placeName key="place_105224" role="date">Cattishall (Cateshull)</placeName> on the morrow of the Ascension of
                  Our Lord, <origDate when="1251-05">35 Hen. III (1251)</origDate>, by which 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Osbert</forename> de <surname>Thorp</surname>
                        </persName> and 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Margaret</forename> his wife</persName> demise to the abbot and 
                  <orgName key="org_104015">church of St. Edmund</orgName> 10s. of annual rent which she had as dowry from the abbot
                  in <placeName key="place_104373">Hinderclay (Hyldercle)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105466">Rickinghall (Rykinghale)</placeName>, and
                  <placeName key="place_105550">Wattisfield (Watlesfeld)</placeName>. For this concession the abbot gave to the said Osbert
                  and Margaret five marks. 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
